  1) chuugoku go nara, hanasemasu
  2) tenisu nara deki masu
  3) sukiyaki nara tsukure masu
  4) go sen en nara kase masu
13-7) I) Translate the following sentences :
  1) mearī san hai chini chini san jikan gurai nihongo o benkyōshimasu
  2) jon san hai-shou kanni i-kai suupa ni ikimasu
  3) anehai-ka getsu ni nikai go rufu o shimasu
  4) ken san hai chi nenni i-kai gaiko kuni ikimasu
13-7) II) Write how often/long you do the following activites, if you aren't certain use gurai :
  1) Talk with your family = zen zen
  2) brush your teeth = ichi nichi ni kaiha o migaki masu
  3) sleep = ichi nichi ni ji chi jikan gurai nemasu
  4) cut your hair = zen zen 
  5) do physical exercise = i-shuukan ni futsuka gurai undou shimasu
  6) catch a cold = zen zen
13-8) I) Answer the questions in Japanese :
  1) ryouri o suru no ga suki desu ka? donna ryouri ga tsukure desu ka? = hay, suki desu, 
  2) kodomo no toki, donna tabemono ga taberare masen deshita ka? = hai, sakana wa tabemasen deshita
  3) ima, isogashii desu ka? (answer with ~shi) = hai。shukudai ga takusan aru shi、repo-to o kaka nakyai kenai shi
  4) kodomo no toki, nani ga shite mita ka-ta desu ka? = kuruma wo-nten shi te mitaka-ta desu
  5) nihon de nani o shite mitai desu ka? = shibuya i-temitai desu
  6) i-shuukan ni nani, nihon go no shukyou ga arimasu ka? = i-shuu kan ni yon juu jikan、nihongo no jugyou ga arimasu
13-8 II) Write about your current part time job, or your former part time job(deshita) :
  1) donna shigoto desu ka? = depato de hatara kima shita
  2) ichi jikan ni iku kuramora imasu ka? = ichi jikan ni senengura imorai mashita
  3) i-shuukan ni nan nichi arubaito o shite imasu ka? = i-shuu kan ni itsu kashite imashita
13-9) A) Listening Comprehension :
  1) nakayama = eigo, iie, ka, sui, moku, kin, nichi
  2) murano =  chuugoku go, hai, getsu, ka, sui, moku, kin
13-9) B) T for true, F for false : 1) T 2) F 3) F 4) T 5) T 6) F 7) T
13-9) C) two people are shopping online :
  1) A) tokei wa taka sou desu
    B) se-ta- wa atataka sou desu
    C) fuetsutonesumashin wa benri sou desu
  2) onna no hito wa tokei o kai masu ka? = kaimasen / doushite desu ka? = taka suki masu kara 
  3) otoko no hito wa se-ta- o kai masu ka? = kaimasu / doushite? = mou sugu otou san no tanjoubi desu kara
  4) onna no hito wa fuetsutonesumashin o kai masu ka? = kaimasu / doushite? = futori mashita kara

=====================================================================================================================Lesson 14: Page 25-31
14-1) I) Write whether or not you want the following :
  1) nuigurumi = nuiguru miga Yoku shikunai desu
  2) yasumi = yasumi ga hoshii desu
  3) okane mochi no tomodachi = okane mochi no tomodachi ga hoshikunai desu 
14-1) II) Write about whether or not you wanted the following when you were a child :
  1) ookii inu = kodomo no toki、ookii inu ga hoshi ka-ta desu
  2) gatsuki = kodomo no toki、ga-ki ga hoshi ka-ta desu
  3) keshouhin = kodomo no toki、keshoshin ga hoshi ka-ta desu
14-1) III) Answer the following questions :
  1) ima, nani ga ichiban wa shiite masu ka? doushite desu ka? = okane ga hoshii desu / atarashii pasokon ga kaitai desu kara
  2) kodomo no toki, nani ga ichiban wa shi ka-ta desu ka? ima mosore ga boshii desu ka? = omocha ga yoku shika-ta desu / ima wa hoshi kunai desu
  3) jikan to okane to dochira ga boshii desu ka? doushite desu ka? = jikan no hou ga hoshii desu / mai nichi isogashi sugi masu kara
14-2) I) Complete the sentences using ~kamo shire masen :
  1) takeshi san wa (stingy) = kera kamo shire masen
  2) yasmin san wa (not interested in kabuki) = kabuki ni kyomi ga nai kamo shire masen
  3) yui san wa (already went home) = mou kae-ta kamo shire masen
  4) meari san wa ima (is in the library) = toshokan ni iru kamo shire masen
  5) kinou no tesuto wa (was not good) = yoku na ka-ta kamo shire masen
14-2) II) Read each situation and make a guess :
  1) kenta san wa itsumo sabishi sou desu = tomodachi ra gai nai kamo shire masen
  2) ai san wa itsumo ie ni imasen = mai nichi arubaito o shi te iru kamo shire masen
  3) kiyou sora san wa ureshi sou desu = kiyou wa sora san no tanjyoubi kamo shire masen
  4) kesa robato san wa totemo nemu sou deshita = kinou no yoru, amari nerarena ka-ta kamo shire masen
14-3) I) The pictures below indicate who gave what to whom, describe using ~akeru / kureru / morau :
  1) ken san wa sora san ni hana o age mashita / sora san wa ken san ni hana o morai mashita
  2) watashi wa sora san ni nuigurumi o age mashita
  3) sora san wa watashi ni Ｔshatsu o kure mashita / watashi wa sora san niＴshatsu o morai mashita
  4) watashi wa ken san ni tokei o age mashita 
  5) ken san wa watashini boushi o kure mashita
14-3) II) Answer the following questions :
  1) tanjyoubi ni nani o morai mashita ka? dare ni morai mashita ka? = birthday what receive? who receive from?
  2) tomodachi no tanjyoubi ni nani o ageru tsumori desu ka? doushite desu ka? = friend birthday what give? why? 
14-4) I) Complete the dialogue using ~tara dou desu ka? :
  1) konban no kaisha de hataraki tain desu (send a resume to a company)= kaisha ni rire kishou o oku-tara dou desu ka?
  2) hajime te de-to o surun desu (go to a stylish restaurant) = asharena resutoran ni i-ta ra dou desu ka? 
  3) netsu ga aru node, kaze kamo shire masen (stay home) = uchi ni i-ta ra dou desu ka? 
  4) tesuto no seiseki ga waru ka-ta n desu (consult with the teacher) = sensei ni sou danshi ta ra dou desu ka? 
  5) saifu o nakushi tan desu (go to the police) = keisatsu ni i-tara dou desu ka? 
14-4) II) make dialogue according to the cues :
  1) What's wrong = doushitan desu ka? 
  2) stating the problem = nihongo no ja kiyou ga muzukashi sugirun desu
  3) giving advice = sensei ni sou danshi tara dou desu ka? 
  4) I will do so, thank you = souji masu, arigatou gozaimasu
